        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Well it just seems to me that there should be a way for me to upgrade to something other than mage summoned stuff.  It seems to me that it would make sense to have some items with just the focus and poor stats that you could obtain just to avoid the hassle of bugging a mage every day.  At the other end of the spectrum, you could have more difficult to acquire items that have a good stats <b>and</b> a desirable focus effect.  Look at the Circlet of the Falinkan, even before this got Affliction Haste 3 tagged on it (surely useful to the same people as Affliction Efficiency) it was probably in the top 5 necro helms in the game.</P><P>It just bugs me to see focus effects that are nice in theory but in practice are too difficult to obtain for it to matter.</P><P>Let me put it this way - since focus effects have gone into the game, <b>none</b> of my gear has changed to something with a focus effect on it.  I get Reanimation Haste 3 (which I personally think should never have gone into the game, it's a far too specific effect for a very minor benefit) and Extended Enhancement 3 from gear I was already wearing before it got focus added.  The only thing different is that I have a Reagent 3 item now that I can swap in if I have the need to use EE's.</P><P>maybe this is a just a pointless rant, I guess.</P><P>-Arbaon, Warlock, Luclin Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
